          </table></p><p>The &#x00A3;6,911,000 increase in the voted element of the resource DEL for RfR l arises from the take up of &#x00A3;66,000,000 of End Year Flexibility provision; the transfer from the Department of Health of &#x00A3;8,120,000 for Healthy Schools Partnerships and Drugs Education; the net transfer to the Department for Work and Pensions of &#x00A3;7,658,000 for the Disability Rights Commission, Adult Basic Skills training arranged through Jobcentre Plus, Administration Costs and the transfer of responsibility for Ranmoor Hall, Sheffield; the net transfer from the Home Office of &#x00A3;2,775,000 for Community Champions, Community Finance and Learning Initiative, shared premises, prison education services, the Mentor Point Initiative, the Black Training and Enterprise Group and Foyer Federation; the</p>
